The paper deals with capacity analysis of wireless communication channels, which is a topic that falls under information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the properties of the channel, such as delay spread and Doppler spread, which are relevant to networking and internet (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of input signals that are peak constrained in time and frequency, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
